title: Packaging Closures and Sealing Systems
description:
Packaging Closures and Sealing Systems by Nigel Theobald

English | 11 Oct. 2006 | ISBN: 1841273376 | 278 Pages | PDF | 5 MB


The packaging closure is the primary interface between the productand the customer. Closures have undergone much evolution anddevelopment in recent years. The basic function of a closure is toallow easy access to a packaged product and to reclose the package,when the contents are not used fully in a single serve
